  <Method>
    <Step image="">Put 1 tbsp butter in saut√© pan and cook shallots until well caramelized. Reduce heat.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add crab, olives, pimiento, herbs and some of the parsley. </Step>
    <Step image="">Add just enough oil to keep contents of pan from sticking.  </Step>
    <Step image="">Cook a few minutes, season with salt and pepper and remove from heat and let set until cool enough to work with. </Step>
    <Step image="">Into each pasta shell, place a slice of cheese and a spoonful of the crab mixture and then set them a greased (buttered!) baking or casserole dish which will accept a cover.  When all of the shells have been stuffed, make sauce. </Step>
    <Step image="">Reheat the pan in which the crab was cooked, deglaze the pan with the white wine and reduce by half.  Add fresh lemon juice to taste -the lemon flavor should be 'there' but not pronounced.  Finish seasoning with salt and pepper, then swirl a tbsp or two of butter through the sauce. </Step>
    <Step image="">Drizzle lemon sauce over them until the dish is about 1/3 filled.  Sprinkle grated parmesan over the top and bake covered for about 20 minutes (just long enough to heat through and melt the provelone cheese). </Step>
    <Step image="">Sprinkle some more of the parsley and it's ready to serve. </Step>
  </Method>
